name: RealCartoon3D
description:
Want to buy me coffee? (Buy a cup)

Please click "read more" to see more detail on the "why" for each version of this model.

**07/03/23: Surprise! Version 3.1 Added. Hope you all enjoy!!

**07/03/23: Added 3.1 Pruned.

**07/03/23: I think Civitai is having issues with download counts, notifications, and such. If I do not respond to a comment, please forgive me.

...Please Share your images...Love seeing the results...

This is my first checkpoint upload. I have been testing out different models (DreamShaper and Duchaitenniji being my favorites) and loras and VAEs to get a look that I really like. This checkpoint merger is a mix of many (I found others with a style I liked, and used them just to influence the overall look). So the weights varied, and I would re-merge to the newly merged checkpoint to get more subtle changes. I was going for a 2.5, realistic, cartoon, anime look. This model does well on a range of LoRAs I have put on it. Along with pretty much being able to do what I ask it to do. I also did not want all the characters to all look asian. I tested it with some various looks and it did alright. I hope the samples give a good idea of the look and abilities.

VAE is Baked in. ALL THE SAMPLES WERE RUN WITHOUT A VAE. MOST ON FULL VERSIONS.

The normal settings I ran it at are as follows:

  • Width: 512 (Have done up to 568)

  • Height: 768 (Have done up to 900)

  • Sampling Method: DPM++ SDE Karras (Also DPM++ 2M Karras and Euler A do well)

  • Sampling steps: 27-30 normally (27 is a nice spot for Euler A)

  • Hires.fix settings: Upscaler (R-ESRGAN 4x+ and 4k-UltraSharp), Hires Steps (10), Denoising Str (0.34 - 0.45 normally), Upscale (2)

  • Clip Skip: 2

  • Ran ADetailer to help enhance the eyes but mainly if I was doing a DPM sampler

About Version 1.0:

First attempt at this. Good base, and does most of what I wanted. Loved the look. I knew I would have other version up; but thought this one was at a good spot to share.

About Version 1.5:

Have done some more subtle updates. Version one is still very nice; but wanting to see what I can do with it as a base now. I also want the checkpoint to do well when you ask for other ethnic types and just general requests period. This version has some samples that are similar to show difference from version one, and a couple to show some of the ability. The two beasts scene has no LoRA.

....All the settings are pretty much the same for getting images from Version one...

Negative prompts I do use often are: BadHandV5, Deep Negative, BadHandV4,

...Would love your feed back on both versions. Thank you for downloading and enjoy!!...

About Version 2.0:

Really been playing around with this version. Keeps the overall look of 1.0/1.5 but gives it a bit of a more "cartoon" look. Thus I feel it should get the 2.0 version. I have really been enjoying the results from this version; especially the eyes on most. I hope you enjoy this model as well.

About Version 2.5:

Ok, so this version is trying to find that balance; to get to what I am going to be calling my final version (3.0) of this model (unless I just get some wow moments in playing around that fit this model's direction). I want to take two paths with this model. One will lean more towards an anime look (Calling it ReadCartoon-Anime) and the other towards a real look (RealCartoon-Realistic). So this model (RealCartoon3D) will be the middle ground. This 2.5 Version just had some really nice results, and I wanted to share them. Again, all the versions do very well; but I am striving for one that just gets most of what I want (for the middle ground that is). :) Hope you all enjoy!!

About Version 3.0:

This Version should be the final. At least for the direction this model is going. This version hits a happy medium (at least for me) between realistic and cartoon. Love the variety and types of people it can create, along with having a good range of prompt ability. I hope you share your images. I really enjoy seeing the results. Please rate as well!! Keeps me motivated to do this. :)

All the samples for this version were done pretty much on Euler A. Just playing with that sampling method at the moment. ADetailer was not enabled for them as well. Still came out rather nicely.

Thank you all for the likes and downloads. I will be uploading an anime version as well soon, but it will be under the Name: RealCartoon-Anime.

About Version 3.1

After some fun working on the Anime and Realistic versions, I was playing around with the base one again. I ended up with this version that I feel does very well in the details and overall response to the prompts, while keeping to what I want RealCartoon3D to be doing. I loved it and felt it needed to be shared. So, here is 3.1 of RealCartoon3D. I hope you all enjoy and continue to share your images. Please rate as well!! I should be getting the pruned version up tomorrow or so. CiVitai has been up and down so, we shall see.
